./sdp/logs/Lead_T-004_20260408T223256Z_1775689515.log:533:./docs/architecture.md:117:The live daemon scheduler also owns a compact half-hour heartbeat. At `:00` and `:30` each hour it sends uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available-agent count, queue progress, and pet XP summary to Telegram, and records the send in Observatory. This is the text-only precursor to the richer GlyphWeave art heartbeat.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-004_20260408T223256Z_1775689515.log:537:./docs/command-reference.md:182:Separately from slash commands, the live daemon now sends a scheduled half-hour heartbeat at `:00` and `:30`. That heartbeat includes uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available agents, queue progress, and pet XP summary, and it is logged to Observatory.
